What you need to know:

Although Djokovic overturned that decision on a technicality on Monday, he is facing possible deportation from Australia if the country's immigration minister decides he has provided false information on his visa form.Djokovic says his agent filled in a form which stated he had not travelled in the 14 days before his arrival, after it emerged he flew from Belgrade to Marbella in Spain during the two weeks before leaving for Melbourne.